# ZION AI Afterburner

## Overview
ZION AI Afterburner is a high-performance AI workload manager designed for the ZION TestNet 2.7.5 ecosystem. It provides real GPU monitoring, AI processing capabilities, and system optimization without simulations.

## Features
- **Real GPU Monitoring**: Live hardware monitoring via nvidia-smi and system sensors
- **AI Processing**: Neural networks, image processing, data analysis, and matrix computations
- **Performance Optimization**: Automatic load balancing and thermal management
- **Systemd Integration**: Production-ready service management
- **Hardware Acceleration**: NVIDIA GPU support for enhanced performance

## Installation
```bash
sudo dpkg -i zion-ai-afterburner-1.0.0.deb
sudo systemctl enable zion-ai-afterburner
sudo systemctl start zion-ai-afterburner
```

## Configuration
Edit `/etc/zion-ai/afterburner.json` to customize settings:
- CPU/GPU usage limits
- Thermal protection thresholds
- AI workload types
- Performance monitoring parameters

## Monitoring
```bash
# Check service status
sudo systemctl status zion-ai-afterburner

# View real-time logs
sudo journalctl -u zion-ai-afterburner -f

# Performance metrics
tail -f /var/lib/zion-ai/logs/afterburner.log
```

## Requirements
- Ubuntu 22.04+ LTS
- Python 3.8+
- 2GB+ RAM (recommended 4GB)
- NVIDIA GPU (optional but recommended)
- psutil and numpy Python packages

## Performance
- Real AI workload processing (no simulations)
- Automatic GPU thermal management
- System resource optimization
- Multi-threaded task processing

For more information, visit: https://github.com/estrelaisabellazion3/Zion-TestNet-2.7.5